@tristaZero Sorry for the late reply, I originally planned to modify the `createRouteValueMap` method in `WhereClauseShardingConditionEngine` class, based on the same column as a group, and then generate the same numeric type in the group. But after trying, I found that there are many implementation classes of the PredicateSegment class, I need to do a lot of meaningless judgment to get the values in the group, and then generate same numeric type value.

```java
private Map<Column, Collection<RouteValue>> createRouteValueMap(final SQLStatementContext sqlStatementContext, final AndPredicate andPredicate, final List<Object> parameters) {
    Map<Column, Collection<RouteValue>> result = new HashMap<>();
    for (PredicateSegment each : andPredicate.getPredicates()) {
        Optional<String> tableName = sqlStatementContext.getTablesContext().findTableName(each.getColumn(), schemaMetaData);
        if (!tableName.isPresent() || !shardingRule.isShardingColumn(each.getColumn().getIdentifier().getValue(), tableName.get())) {
            continue;
        }
        Column column = new Column(each.getColumn().getIdentifier().getValue(), tableName.get());
        Optional<RouteValue> routeValue = ConditionValueGeneratorFactory.generate(each.getRightValue(), column, parameters);
        if (!routeValue.isPresent()) {
            continue;
        }
        if (!result.containsKey(column)) {
            result.put(column, new LinkedList<>());
        }
        result.get(column).add(routeValue.get());
    }
    return result;
}
```

So I tried the second solution you suggested, and made some conversions where the Range operation was performed. I have submitted a [PR](https://github.com/apache/shardingsphere/pull/5770), can you help me review it? 😃 

BTW, I also tried the first solution, and all returned BigInteger types, which would cause many existing unit tests to report errors, so I still prefer the second method.
